LPreview: Framework-Agnostic Preview Module Documentation
1. Overview
LPreview is a bridge developed to render video sources (LObject) across different UI systems. The pointer (void*) passed to the previewEnable method is automatically processed according to the framework being used (Qt QWidget* or GTK GtkWidget*).
2. Architectural Structure
    • PIMPL Pattern: LPreview encapsulates interface details under an Impl class. This ensures the main project only needs to know about LPreview.h, while the underlying Qt or GTK engines handle the implementation.
    • Framework Selection: The engine can be switched at runtime using the setProps("ui_framework", "qt") or "gtk" command.
3. Usage Examples
A. Usage with Qt (on QWidget)
To embed a preview into a QWidget in Qt projects:
C++
#include "LPreview.h"

// Inside MainWindow constructor or setup
LPreview* preview = new LPreview();
preview->setProps("ui_framework", "qt");
preview->setProps("scale_type", "aspect-ratio");

// ui->videoFrame is a QWidget pointer
preview->previewEnable(ui->videoFrame, true, true); 
preview->previewObject(myLObjectSource);
B. Usage with GTK (on GtkWidget)
To embed a preview into a GtkBox or GtkWindow in GTK projects:
C++
#include "LPreview.h"

LPreview* preview = new LPreview();
preview->setProps("ui_framework", "gtk");
preview->setProps("preview_background", "gray");

// Pass your GtkBox or GtkWindow widget as the parent
preview->previewEnable(myGtkBox, true, true);
preview->previewObject(myLObjectSource);
4. Technical Specifications and Prop Settings
Prop Key	Values	Description
ui_framework	"qt", "gtk"	Determines which render engine to use.
scale_type	"aspect-ratio", "crop"	Sets the fitting mode of the video within the frame.
audio_meter	"true", "false"	Activates/deactivates audio level meters.
preview_background	"black", "gray", etc.	Sets the background color.
5. Statistics and Status Management
    • previewObject(LObject* source): Connects the live camera (LLive) or file (LFile) object to be previewed.
    • statusGet(int& status): Checks whether the preview is currently on the screen.
    • setName() / setStatus(): Used to write dynamic text or status information (e.g., "On Air", "Offline") over the preview window.
Important Notes
    • Dynamic Changes: After previewEnable is called, changing settings via setProps updates the internalWidget objects instantly.
    • Resource Cleanup: When the LPreview object is destroyed, the background objects (LVideoWidget for Qt or LVideoWidgetGTK for GTK) are automatically cleaned up from memory.
This module is a critical layer, especially for systems that require multi-platform support or want to use different UI technologies within the same project (hybrid). 
